1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,680
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,680 --> 00:00:03,136
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,467 --> 00:00:05,933
Yes, Eun Nim.

4
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:08,775
She dropped out last year.

5
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:12,033
Dropped out?

6
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,533
That's impossible. That can't be.

7
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,473
Are you okay?

8
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,556
No, that can't be. Why would Eun Nim...

9
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:26,167
I'm sorry, I have to go to class now.

10
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:32,633
No, it can't be. It isn't, right?

11
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:50,217
Is this the office of academic affairs
of Haedeul University?

12
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:55,021
I'm the mother of a medical student.

13
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:59,922
I have something to check. Yes.

14
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:02,800
No, you...

15
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:07,046
Yes, the student ID is...

16
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:13,473
Her name is Cho Eun Nim.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,778
Is there really no way at all?

18
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:21,733
Even something to slow the progression...

19
00:01:21,733 --> 00:01:24,351
If there were,
we would've done it long ago.

20
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:27,754
At this point,
all we can do is prescribe painkillers...

21
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:31,558
and patches to ease the pain.

22
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,400
I'm sorry.

23
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:44,805
What on earth happened?

24
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,867
You dropped out a year ago?

25
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:49,713
I'm sorry, Dad.

26
00:01:49,713 --> 00:01:51,713
Sorry isn't the issue right now.

27
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:55,300
How could you keep something this big
a secret for a whole year?

28
00:01:57,084 --> 00:01:58,385
(Mom)

29
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,433
Hi, Mom.

30
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:09,763
Cho Eun Nim,
I'm in front of the ER right now.

31
00:02:11,032 --> 00:02:13,834
When will you be done? I'll wait.

32
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:15,033
No, Mom.

33
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:17,037
I don't think I'll have any time today,

34
00:02:17,037 --> 00:02:18,105
so just go home.

35
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,609
Are you that busy? Then I'll come in
and at least give you the lunch...

36
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:24,800
Mom, the professor is calling me. Bye.

37
00:02:30,293 --> 00:02:31,293
How come you're all here?

38
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,100
Why? What's the matter?

39
00:02:42,899 --> 00:02:43,899
To the very end...

40
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,301
She lied to the very end...

41
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,408
Are you okay?

42
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:04,340
Thank you.

43
00:03:08,267 --> 00:03:10,190
I didn't mean to overhear.

44
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:14,733
It must hurt a lot, right?

45
00:03:20,153 --> 00:03:21,519
As a mom,

46
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,600
I had no idea
my daughter had dropped out...

47
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:27,474
for over a year.

48
00:03:29,053 --> 00:03:30,319
How is this even possible?

49
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,667
How could my own child,
whom I gave birth to,

50
00:03:35,086 --> 00:03:37,720
betray me like this?

51
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:42,622
I don't know if this will comfort you,

52
00:03:44,259 --> 00:03:46,559
but it's better for a child...

53
00:03:48,506 --> 00:03:50,739
to betray the mom than for a mom...

54
00:03:52,587 --> 00:03:54,301
to betray her child.

55
00:03:57,044 --> 00:03:58,900
A child betrayed by their mom...

56
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:03,300
is as good as abandoned
by the whole world.

57
00:04:04,652 --> 00:04:07,019
Imagine that child...

58
00:04:07,019 --> 00:04:09,453
carrying that wound for life.

59
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,019
For parents,

60
00:04:14,059 --> 00:04:16,493
their child's pain hurts more
than their own.

61
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:22,028
That's right. That's how most moms are.

62
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,933
But some aren't.

63
00:04:28,136 --> 00:04:29,136
Sorry?

64
00:04:32,033 --> 00:04:34,541
Some people value their own lives
more than their children,

65
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,300
and they...

66
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:42,101
But now that I've experienced it,

67
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:46,886
being betrayed by your child
hurts a lot too.

68
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:50,133
I'm being foolish.

69
00:04:51,448 --> 00:04:54,800
I'm sorry for saying such things...

70
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,664
when you're hurting over your child.

71
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:58,833
It's okay.

72
00:04:59,802 --> 00:05:02,769
But why are you here like this?

73
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:03,933
Me?

74
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,577
My husband is very ill,

75
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:14,067
and they say
there's nothing more they can do.

76
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,383
My goodness...

77
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:19,786
I want to grasp at straws,

78
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:25,400
but there's not even a thread
to hold onto.

79
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:29,963
No wonder you look so pale.

80
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:37,570
But still, hang in there.

81
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:41,541
I'll get going now.

82
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:43,767
There must be...

83
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,346
some other reason...

84
00:05:47,193 --> 00:05:50,884
why your daughter dropped out.
Please look into it carefully.

85
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:53,833
Yes, I will.

86
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,267
Ma'am.

87
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:02,004
Don't forget this.

88
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:04,233
Yes.

89
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,839
Excuse me, ma'am.

90
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:13,133
Would you like to share this lunch
with me?

91
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:14,241
Sorry?

92
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:18,367
I packed it for my daughter,

93
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:21,714
but taking it back feels so heavy.

94
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,817
But we just met...

95
00:06:24,867 --> 00:06:28,357
I made plenty,
thinking I'd eat it with my daughter.

96
00:06:28,956 --> 00:06:31,033
You put a lot of care into this.

97
00:06:31,413 --> 00:06:33,493
I'm not sure if I should eat it.

98
00:06:38,113 --> 00:06:39,833
It's hot,
so please blow on it before eating.

99
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,737
It's been simmered very well.

100
00:06:49,106 --> 00:06:51,740
My husband is lying sick,

101
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,934
yet I can still eat like this.

102
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:58,393
Of course you should eat.

103
00:06:58,393 --> 00:06:59,933
The patient matters,

104
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:03,300
but the caregiver needs to eat well
to take care of them.

105
00:07:08,695 --> 00:07:10,632
I brought chopsticks too.

106
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:14,233
- And some rice.
- You brought so much.

107
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:15,534
Cho Eun Nim.

108
00:07:15,999 --> 00:07:19,033
How could you do this? All this time...

109
00:07:19,453 --> 00:07:21,553
I was suffering too.

110
00:07:22,978 --> 00:07:24,745
I was going to tell you eventually,

111
00:07:25,145 --> 00:07:26,278
but I wanted to achieve something...

112
00:07:26,745 --> 00:07:29,578
with what I wanted to do first.

113
00:07:29,578 --> 00:07:31,211
Does that even make sense?

114
00:07:32,478 --> 00:07:35,111
More than you dropping out,

115
00:07:35,445 --> 00:07:37,811
what I can't understand
is how you kept this...

116
00:07:37,811 --> 00:07:39,398
from your family for a whole year.

117
00:07:39,398 --> 00:07:41,345
Maybe this isn't the time to say it,

118
00:07:41,837 --> 00:07:43,237
but isn't that the same for you, Dad?

119
00:07:43,511 --> 00:07:45,245
Are your situation and his the same?

120
00:07:45,711 --> 00:07:47,578
For your expensive medical school tuition,
Dad...

121
00:07:47,578 --> 00:07:50,211
I told you I saved all that money
in the bank.

122
00:07:50,565 --> 00:07:52,631
I was going to return it
when I told the truth.

123
00:07:52,631 --> 00:07:55,542
So what, do you want praise for that?

124
00:07:55,542 --> 00:07:57,511
Wait, let's not argue.

125
00:07:58,545 --> 00:08:00,644
In a situation like this,
we should first think about reaching...

126
00:08:00,644 --> 00:08:02,849
the most rational
and reasonable conclusion.

127
00:08:04,118 --> 00:08:07,245
Right, let's at least hear the reason.

128
00:08:07,245 --> 00:08:08,878
It's not a leave of absence.
You dropped out.

129
00:08:09,491 --> 00:08:10,924
There must've been a reason for that.

130
00:08:13,963 --> 00:08:16,796
I have a fear of blood.

131
00:08:19,254 --> 00:08:21,937
Even seeing a small cut on a finger
or a needle...

132
00:08:21,938 --> 00:08:24,838
makes me tremble and struggle to breathe.

133
00:08:26,059 --> 00:08:27,978
I fainted on the spot when I saw...

134
00:08:27,978 --> 00:08:29,642
a patient bleeding during ER practice.

135
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:34,147
Is that like panic disorder or something?

136
00:08:34,945 --> 00:08:35,978
Something like that.

137
00:08:36,765 --> 00:08:39,598
Even in first-year anatomy class,
I would vomit and collapse.

138
00:08:40,892 --> 00:08:44,224
Dad, how can someone like me
become a doctor?

139
00:08:45,478 --> 00:08:48,045
If that happened, you should've told us,

140
00:08:48,278 --> 00:08:50,311
and we could've decided together.

141
00:08:51,145 --> 00:08:52,145
What do we do now?

142
00:08:53,292 --> 00:08:57,025
Mom has already suffered so much
because of me and Eun Hyeong.

143
00:08:57,671 --> 00:08:58,971
If she finds out about Eun Nim too...

144
00:08:59,439 --> 00:09:00,874
This is really bad.

145
00:09:01,711 --> 00:09:04,511
She probably hasn't even healed
from what I put her through yet.

146
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:08,681
(Wife)

147
00:09:14,258 --> 00:09:17,484
Hey, honey. Where are you going?

148
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:21,461
I'm not at the office right now.
I'm working outside.

149
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,811
Okay, see you at home later.

150
00:09:27,078 --> 00:09:28,434
Why did Mom suddenly call?

151
00:09:29,204 --> 00:09:31,671
Do you think she already found out
about Eun Nim?

152
00:09:32,098 --> 00:09:35,564
I don't know. Her voice didn't sound good.

153
00:09:38,657 --> 00:09:40,246
How did all of us end up doing this
to your mom?

154
00:09:41,991 --> 00:09:43,525
We really shouldn't have.

155
00:09:44,425 --> 00:09:46,658
I'm going to tell Mom everything today.

156
00:09:47,045 --> 00:09:48,401
She's going to find out anyway.

157
00:09:48,401 --> 00:09:50,361
Look at you,
acting like a conquering hero.

158
00:09:50,361 --> 00:09:51,591
What are you so proud of?

159
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,078
Why shouldn't I be?

160
00:09:53,645 --> 00:09:55,511
I'm going to come clean and start fresh,

161
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:56,729
and do my work honestly.

162
00:09:57,178 --> 00:10:00,032
So you want to push Mom to the edge
just so you can start fresh?

163
00:10:00,638 --> 00:10:03,005
You should at least
prepare something objective...

164
00:10:03,331 --> 00:10:06,139
to minimize the shock for her.

165
00:10:08,978 --> 00:10:11,578
Right, what about you?
You said you had something to discuss.

166
00:10:12,038 --> 00:10:14,071
Right now, Eun Nim's situation
is overwhelming enough.

167
00:10:14,445 --> 00:10:15,548
I'll talk about mine later.

168
00:10:16,938 --> 00:10:18,938
We're still working, so until we finish,

169
00:10:19,245 --> 00:10:21,221
you two stay here and come up with a plan.

170
00:10:21,221 --> 00:10:22,455
- Got it?
- Yes.

171
00:10:24,278 --> 00:10:26,545
Don't do anything rash...

172
00:10:26,545 --> 00:10:28,045
unless you want to make Mom collapse.

173
00:10:37,211 --> 00:10:39,672
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, let's talk for a moment.

174
00:10:40,178 --> 00:10:41,311
Yes, Manager Seo.

175
00:10:47,045 --> 00:10:49,445
I want to apologize for what I said
at the hospital before.

176
00:10:50,385 --> 00:10:52,485
I was too sensitive. I'm sorry.

177
00:10:52,845 --> 00:10:53,878
It's okay.

178
00:10:54,091 --> 00:10:57,124
You're practically part of
Team Manager's family,

179
00:10:57,471 --> 00:11:00,638
and I overstepped. I apologize again.

180
00:11:01,851 --> 00:11:03,963
- Well, then.
- Manager Seo.

181
00:11:05,111 --> 00:11:07,478
There's something I'd like to say.

182
00:11:08,236 --> 00:11:10,670
I think you misunderstood something.

183
00:11:11,298 --> 00:11:12,498
- Misunderstood?
- Yes.

184
00:11:12,961 --> 00:11:16,778
When I said,
"I like it very much" last night,

185
00:11:16,778 --> 00:11:19,711
I didn't mean the Team Manager.
I meant Joy.

186
00:11:20,244 --> 00:11:23,016
The Team Manager finally gave me access
to Joy's server.

187
00:11:24,478 --> 00:11:25,645
I didn't misunderstand.

188
00:11:25,978 --> 00:11:28,278
I'm not curious enough
to need that kind of explanation.

189
00:11:28,278 --> 00:11:29,689
Right?

190
00:11:30,545 --> 00:11:33,726
Anyway,
I'm glad there was no misunderstanding.

191
00:11:34,745 --> 00:11:36,811
Now that you have access to the server,
you should work hard.

192
00:11:37,345 --> 00:11:38,845
If you get good results
in this competition,

193
00:11:38,845 --> 00:11:41,111
it'll be a great opportunity for you too.

194
00:11:41,378 --> 00:11:43,011
Yes, I understand.

195
00:11:46,591 --> 00:11:49,691
Manager Seo really is amazing.

196
00:12:00,331 --> 00:12:03,098
Why are you all coming in together?

197
00:12:05,211 --> 00:12:06,978
Eun Nim, I need to talk to you.

198
00:12:06,978 --> 00:12:08,778
Let's talk here, all together.

199
00:12:10,545 --> 00:12:11,898
Do you know what I'm going to say?

200
00:12:12,378 --> 00:12:14,611
Mom, I dropped out a year ago.

201
00:12:15,404 --> 00:12:17,604
I'm not a medical student anymore.

202
00:12:18,211 --> 00:12:19,278
Look at you...

203
00:12:20,411 --> 00:12:22,862
Honey, did you hear what she said?

204
00:12:22,862 --> 00:12:26,112
She says she dropped out secretly.
And a year ago, at that.

205
00:12:27,278 --> 00:12:30,082
- Everyone, sit down.
- Why sit?

206
00:12:32,599 --> 00:12:35,165
Why aren't you surprised?

207
00:12:36,358 --> 00:12:38,758
Did all of you know already?

208
00:12:39,534 --> 00:12:41,311
Mom, actually...

209
00:12:41,311 --> 00:12:44,097
Was I the only one
who didn't know again? Just me?

210
00:12:44,445 --> 00:12:46,633
We just found out this afternoon too.

211
00:12:47,811 --> 00:12:50,878
First, you should hear
why Eun Nim had to drop out...

212
00:12:51,491 --> 00:12:53,039
and what happened.

213
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,665
You say it yourself.

214
00:12:54,665 --> 00:12:55,711
That's right.

215
00:12:55,911 --> 00:12:59,145
I have a fear of blood,
so I can't become a doctor.

216
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,455
A fear of blood?

217
00:13:03,111 --> 00:13:05,562
Who is fine with seeing blood?

218
00:13:05,562 --> 00:13:07,411
Everyone's scared of blood.

219
00:13:07,611 --> 00:13:10,356
You quit med school
because you're scared of that?

220
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:12,978
It's not just being scared.
I couldn't endure it.

221
00:13:13,645 --> 00:13:16,474
I fainted multiple times
and couldn't take it anymore.

222
00:13:16,818 --> 00:13:17,818
Fainted?

223
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:22,435
If it was that serious,
why didn't you ever talk to us?

224
00:13:22,771 --> 00:13:25,611
Why did you pretend to go to school
and lie for a whole year? Why?

225
00:13:25,611 --> 00:13:28,278
This is exactly why!
Because you're like this, Mom.

226
00:13:29,212 --> 00:13:30,345
What did I do?

227
00:13:30,731 --> 00:13:32,664
Every time you saw me,
you called me "Dr. Cho."

228
00:13:33,698 --> 00:13:36,232
You acted like me becoming a doctor
was your life's dream.

229
00:13:37,078 --> 00:13:38,145
Please.

230
00:13:39,021 --> 00:13:41,721
Mom, calm down, please.

231
00:13:42,045 --> 00:13:43,389
It's my life anyway.

232
00:13:44,111 --> 00:13:46,111
You're not going to live it for me.

233
00:13:46,445 --> 00:13:48,594
Why should I walk a path I can't take
just because of you?

234
00:13:48,758 --> 00:13:49,858
Unbelievable.

235
00:13:50,545 --> 00:13:52,585
Are you saying I ruined your life?

236
00:13:52,585 --> 00:13:54,285
No, that's not it.

237
00:13:55,711 --> 00:13:57,678
I wanted to be honest,

238
00:13:58,832 --> 00:14:00,873
but whenever I saw your face,
I couldn't speak.

239
00:14:01,824 --> 00:14:03,591
I've succeeded with a web novel
in my own way.

240
00:14:04,013 --> 00:14:06,646
I'm building a life doing what I want
and what I'm good at.

241
00:14:06,911 --> 00:14:07,911
A web novel?

242
00:14:08,991 --> 00:14:11,978
Then that medical novel I saw
on your laptop before...

243
00:14:11,978 --> 00:14:14,245
Yes, I wrote it.

244
00:14:15,710 --> 00:14:19,044
It's my decision for my life,
so respect it.

245
00:14:25,134 --> 00:14:28,601
Mom, I'm sorry we keep taking turns
causing you stress.

246
00:14:28,891 --> 00:14:31,411
Are you all waiting in line...

247
00:14:31,411 --> 00:14:33,245
to take me down one by one?

248
00:14:33,413 --> 00:14:35,325
Why are you all doing this to me?

249
00:14:36,145 --> 00:14:37,245
I'm sorry, Mom.

250
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:40,512
But I've experienced it, so I know.

251
00:14:41,011 --> 00:14:43,011
If it's not your path, you can't walk it.

252
00:14:44,378 --> 00:14:47,678
Honey, since it's come to this,
let's trust her.

253
00:14:48,405 --> 00:14:51,411
Eun Nim has always handled
her own matters well.

254
00:14:51,411 --> 00:14:52,479
She'll do the same this time.

255
00:14:52,479 --> 00:14:54,727
You can say that even in this situation?

256
00:14:55,078 --> 00:14:56,831
After being completely deceived
for over a year,

257
00:14:56,831 --> 00:14:59,165
how can you talk like a saint?

258
00:15:14,218 --> 00:15:15,481
What do you mean?

259
00:15:15,685 --> 00:15:18,851
Father said the safe password
is that child's birthday?

260
00:15:19,545 --> 00:15:20,753
That's what he said.

261
00:15:21,278 --> 00:15:23,723
But the problem is,
I tried Gyeol's birthday...

262
00:15:23,723 --> 00:15:26,446
and everyone else's in the family,
and none worked.

263
00:15:28,045 --> 00:15:29,811
Who on earth is that child?

264
00:15:31,045 --> 00:15:34,711
Could Father have another child
besides you?

265
00:15:35,104 --> 00:15:37,109
Come on. No way.

266
00:15:37,551 --> 00:15:39,918
I'm his only child, the only one.

267
00:15:40,145 --> 00:15:41,511
The sole legitimate heir.

268
00:15:41,511 --> 00:15:43,409
Then maybe Mother?

269
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:45,611
What?

270
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:48,024
Last time, I said I saw a cheap pendant...

271
00:15:48,024 --> 00:15:49,945
while rummaging through the cabinet,
right?

272
00:15:51,098 --> 00:15:53,998
Could there be some secret inside it?

273
00:15:55,711 --> 00:15:57,711
My goodness, Crystal.

274
00:15:57,950 --> 00:15:59,818
I thought you were just transparent,

275
00:15:59,818 --> 00:16:02,829
but you sparkle too.

276
00:16:03,751 --> 00:16:04,751
Get up, hurry.

277
00:16:05,258 --> 00:16:08,125
Father is being discharged tomorrow,
so today is our only chance.

278
00:16:08,365 --> 00:16:09,831
Suivez-moi. Come with me.

279
00:16:11,184 --> 00:16:13,076
What does that even mean?

280
00:16:19,711 --> 00:16:21,211
Why? It's not there?

281
00:16:21,211 --> 00:16:23,146
It was definitely here.

282
00:16:28,551 --> 00:16:30,722
Crystal, why did you turn on the light?

283
00:16:30,722 --> 00:16:33,811
What else am I supposed to do?
I can't find anything like this.

284
00:16:33,811 --> 00:16:35,475
Move, I'll check this side.

285
00:16:37,064 --> 00:16:38,331
Careful.

286
00:16:50,578 --> 00:16:52,044
My heart almost stopped.

287
00:16:52,044 --> 00:16:54,347
Be careful.

288
00:16:55,145 --> 00:16:58,591
Wait, would Father really
put a necklace...

289
00:16:58,591 --> 00:17:00,453
he doesn't even know about in the safe?

290
00:17:01,105 --> 00:17:02,388
Careful.

291
00:17:02,388 --> 00:17:04,123
Okay, careful.

292
00:17:04,311 --> 00:17:05,311
Be quiet.

293
00:17:09,418 --> 00:17:10,418
You scared me.

294
00:17:12,578 --> 00:17:15,011
Did you come home together?

295
00:17:15,011 --> 00:17:18,011
Yes, after working late,
we came together in my car.

296
00:17:18,505 --> 00:17:19,905
But what are you doing here?

297
00:17:20,278 --> 00:17:22,545
We were just...

298
00:17:22,545 --> 00:17:26,111
Your grandpa is coming back,
so we're tidying the room.

299
00:17:26,111 --> 00:17:27,579
This looks better, right?

300
00:17:27,824 --> 00:17:29,114
Tidying the room, yes.

301
00:17:29,645 --> 00:17:31,578
Don't you know how to knock?

302
00:17:32,011 --> 00:17:34,477
We heard something from an empty room.
Sorry.

303
00:17:40,417 --> 00:17:42,228
All right, go upstairs and rest.

304
00:17:43,518 --> 00:17:46,618
What do we do? Do you think they noticed?

305
00:17:46,618 --> 00:17:48,746
I don't know. Retreat, let's go.

306
00:17:48,978 --> 00:17:50,357
- My heart almost gave out.
- Get out.

307
00:18:01,078 --> 00:18:04,345
What have they been looking for
in Grandpa's room?

308
00:18:06,719 --> 00:18:09,021
(Childish Bunny)

309
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:14,851
Are you still working?

310
00:18:15,578 --> 00:18:17,563
Sorry I left early.

311
00:18:23,385 --> 00:18:24,385
It's fine.

312
00:18:27,504 --> 00:18:30,743
Is something wrong?

313
00:18:32,472 --> 00:18:34,147
No, it's nothing.

314
00:18:34,549 --> 00:18:37,316
I'll work harder starting tomorrow.
Good night.

315
00:18:40,078 --> 00:18:42,845
"Good night." Right...

316
00:18:45,678 --> 00:18:46,778
Good night.

317
00:18:48,411 --> 00:18:50,229
Sweet dreams.

318
00:18:51,111 --> 00:18:55,067
"Sweet dreams?" That's a bit...

319
00:18:59,207 --> 00:19:00,373
Can't be nice.

320
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:08,848
(Not-So-Noble Ko Gyeol sent an image,
Dream of me.)

321
00:19:10,278 --> 00:19:11,278
What?

322
00:19:12,211 --> 00:19:14,052
What is this?

323
00:19:15,205 --> 00:19:16,823
"Dream of me?"

324
00:19:18,624 --> 00:19:20,559
Min Ho, what's going on?

325
00:19:21,078 --> 00:19:22,578
Grandpa is getting discharged tomorrow,

326
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:24,478
so let's go to the hospital together
in my car in the morning.

327
00:19:25,437 --> 00:19:26,629
If the timing works out, okay.

328
00:19:27,652 --> 00:19:29,735
Were you texting?

329
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:31,170
No, it's nothing.

330
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,271
(Dream of me.)

331
00:19:34,338 --> 00:19:35,874
Why are you so flustered?

332
00:19:36,114 --> 00:19:39,412
What? No, it's nothing.

333
00:19:40,478 --> 00:19:41,578
- All right.
- Okay.

334
00:19:41,578 --> 00:19:43,582
- Good night.
- Yeah, good night.

335
00:19:49,411 --> 00:19:50,411
What is this?

336
00:19:50,811 --> 00:19:52,858
Why did this send?

337
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:54,093
(Dream of me.)

338
00:19:55,545 --> 00:19:58,078
Good thing it hasn't been read yet.

339
00:19:59,325 --> 00:20:00,378
I should delete it.

340
00:20:00,378 --> 00:20:01,378
(Delete)

341
00:20:02,359 --> 00:20:03,359
Delete.

342
00:20:05,578 --> 00:20:06,850
That scared me.

343
00:20:10,611 --> 00:20:13,478
Was Eun Nim's situation that shocking?

344
00:20:14,378 --> 00:20:15,547
Why is my heart racing?

345
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:31,237
What's with your expression?

346
00:20:32,505 --> 00:20:35,000
Are you nervous about your first lecture
as a full-time professor?

347
00:20:35,778 --> 00:20:38,604
Yeah, a bit.

348
00:20:38,911 --> 00:20:41,911
Maybe it's because you worked so hard
to get out of unemployment.

349
00:20:43,345 --> 00:20:44,744
Let's have a party tomorrow.

350
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:47,445
A celebration
for Professor Cho Eun Hyeong.

351
00:20:48,859 --> 00:20:50,415
- Sounds good.
- No.

352
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:52,518
Don't do that.

353
00:20:54,038 --> 00:20:57,390
Good things
should be celebrated together, Dad.

354
00:20:58,445 --> 00:20:59,579
Thank you for the meal.

355
00:20:59,579 --> 00:21:01,393
- I'll go brush my teeth.
- Okay.

356
00:21:04,078 --> 00:21:05,078
Okay...

357
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:10,136
(Kangsu Construction)

358
00:21:11,578 --> 00:21:13,605
- Good morning.
- Hello.

359
00:21:16,385 --> 00:21:18,311
So this is based on the sketch.

360
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:22,214
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, how is Joy coming along?

361
00:21:22,214 --> 00:21:23,315
Don't worry.

362
00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:25,611
I'll organize the overall plan soon
and send it to you.

363
00:21:25,971 --> 00:21:29,338
And from today until the competition,
I'll be working overtime every day.

364
00:21:29,586 --> 00:21:31,290
If necessary, I'll even pull all-nighters.

365
00:21:31,878 --> 00:21:33,292
There's no need for a good night.

366
00:21:33,611 --> 00:21:35,327
Sorry? "Good night?"

367
00:21:35,895 --> 00:21:38,097
No, I mean,

368
00:21:38,678 --> 00:21:40,966
do you really need to pull all-nighters?

369
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,468
Okay.

370
00:21:44,278 --> 00:21:45,371
Team Manager,

371
00:21:46,405 --> 00:21:48,374
about that message...

372
00:21:48,925 --> 00:21:51,310
- What?
- No, it's nothing.

373
00:21:55,319 --> 00:21:57,684
Did she read it or not?

374
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:01,854
(Due to personal circumstances,
this episode has been postponed.)

375
00:22:03,078 --> 00:22:04,289
What's going on?

376
00:22:05,358 --> 00:22:07,767
It's never been postponed before.

377
00:22:09,711 --> 00:22:12,565
Should I just rejoin the chat?

378
00:22:14,425 --> 00:22:17,525
Yeah, I will.
I can just change my nickname.

379
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:21,571
Genius Seo?

380
00:22:25,151 --> 00:22:26,645
Since my last name is Seo...

381
00:22:27,247 --> 00:22:28,446
S Dragon?

382
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,520
Okay.

383
00:22:35,511 --> 00:22:38,257
(ER King)

384
00:22:39,552 --> 00:22:42,061
Okay, joined.

385
00:22:42,061 --> 00:22:44,063
(ER King's post is trending fast.)

386
00:22:45,445 --> 00:22:47,611
It's never been postponed before.

387
00:22:48,479 --> 00:22:49,835
Does anyone know why?

388
00:22:53,345 --> 00:22:54,578
Don't worry too much.

389
00:22:55,241 --> 00:22:57,607
The author has been working nonstop,

390
00:22:58,092 --> 00:23:00,058
so maybe they're just not feeling well.

391
00:23:00,645 --> 00:23:01,712
They'll be back soon.

392
00:23:02,185 --> 00:23:06,018
Really? I hope so.

393
00:23:07,558 --> 00:23:10,658
There are readers waiting for my novel
like this.

394
00:23:12,604 --> 00:23:13,992
I should pull myself together.

395
00:23:16,138 --> 00:23:20,165
"The ER Witch" will continue
starting tomorrow.

396
00:23:22,201 --> 00:23:23,640
Thanks for the info.

397
00:23:25,945 --> 00:23:29,108
Are you close to the author, by the way?

398
00:23:30,578 --> 00:23:33,245
What? No.

399
00:23:34,011 --> 00:23:35,447
Why do you think that?

400
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:38,284
Your comment sounded so certain.

401
00:23:41,675 --> 00:23:45,015
That's because, as a longtime reader,

402
00:23:45,211 --> 00:23:47,178
I trust the author.

403
00:23:50,151 --> 00:23:52,330
I see. Thank you.

404
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,522
(Crazy Anne)

405
00:23:54,522 --> 00:23:57,709
That nickname is totally my type.

406
00:23:58,869 --> 00:23:59,891
"Crazy"...

407
00:24:03,378 --> 00:24:04,678
Wait.

408
00:24:04,678 --> 00:24:05,978
Careful, Father, slowly.

409
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:09,048
Watch your step on the stairs.

410
00:24:09,411 --> 00:24:12,245
Congratulations on your discharge, Father.

411
00:24:13,622 --> 00:24:14,719
Being all fussy...

412
00:24:15,838 --> 00:24:16,989
Why?

413
00:24:17,478 --> 00:24:20,225
Your children are happy
about your discharge.

414
00:24:21,045 --> 00:24:25,151
Of course. I'd even like
to shout "Hurray" three times.

415
00:24:26,058 --> 00:24:27,311
What?

416
00:24:27,311 --> 00:24:29,011
Then, instead of that,

417
00:24:29,011 --> 00:24:30,945
should I sing a congratulatory song?

418
00:24:31,278 --> 00:24:33,545
I used to dream
of being a musical actress.

419
00:24:34,506 --> 00:24:35,811
Not a bad idea.

420
00:24:35,811 --> 00:24:39,145
Pick the right time and place.

421
00:24:41,511 --> 00:24:43,178
Congratulations on your discharge,
Chairman.

422
00:24:44,185 --> 00:24:45,419
Welcome, Jeong Ran.

423
00:24:45,743 --> 00:24:49,912
Thanks to the soup I had at the hospital,
I feel great.

424
00:24:50,945 --> 00:24:53,792
Thank you for saying that.

425
00:24:53,792 --> 00:24:55,311
What did you bring this time?

426
00:24:55,545 --> 00:24:57,345
I went to the fish market early...

427
00:24:57,518 --> 00:25:00,351
and made abalone porridge
with fresh abalone.

428
00:25:00,911 --> 00:25:02,934
You really went all out.

429
00:25:03,135 --> 00:25:05,345
I'll head to the annex.

430
00:25:07,858 --> 00:25:09,392
I'll get going too.

431
00:25:10,078 --> 00:25:12,211
All right, good work.

432
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:14,246
And about what I asked you to check,

433
00:25:14,978 --> 00:25:16,915
let me know as soon as it's confirmed.

434
00:25:20,311 --> 00:25:23,030
I just arrived, I'll go on my own.

435
00:25:24,884 --> 00:25:25,884
I'll get going then.

436
00:25:29,111 --> 00:25:31,163
- Why aren't you leaving?
- Sorry?

437
00:25:31,345 --> 00:25:33,745
Only family is left here now,

438
00:25:33,911 --> 00:25:35,645
so why are you still here?

439
00:25:35,645 --> 00:25:37,569
Don't say that.

440
00:25:39,071 --> 00:25:41,974
Jeong Ran,
stay and have lunch with us later.

441
00:25:42,918 --> 00:25:44,343
Yes, ma'am.

442
00:25:46,111 --> 00:25:49,281
Go inside and rest until lunchtime.

443
00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:50,977
- All right, let's go in.
- Yes.

444
00:25:50,977 --> 00:25:51,977
Be careful.

445
00:25:51,977 --> 00:25:53,226
- Careful, slowly.
- Father.

446
00:25:53,226 --> 00:25:54,226
Take it easy.

447
00:25:54,226 --> 00:25:55,311
- Slowly.
- Don't overdo it.

448
00:25:55,311 --> 00:25:56,655
- Slowly.
- Slowly.

449
00:25:57,758 --> 00:26:02,465
Home really is the best.

450
00:26:04,811 --> 00:26:06,698
I feel sleepy already.

451
00:26:32,578 --> 00:26:35,111
Mother, I'll take this vase.

452
00:26:35,791 --> 00:26:39,495
Stop. He just fell asleep. Go on out.

453
00:26:39,999 --> 00:26:41,901
Okay...

454
00:27:09,511 --> 00:27:12,778
Is this a study room?
Everyone's working so hard.

455
00:27:13,978 --> 00:27:15,200
If you're going to keep working,

456
00:27:15,645 --> 00:27:17,645
should we all go out
and have dinner together?

457
00:27:18,572 --> 00:27:20,938
I don't have time, so you go ahead.

458
00:27:21,173 --> 00:27:23,178
Should our team just order takeout?

459
00:27:23,178 --> 00:27:25,011
Yes, I'll order right away.

460
00:27:25,278 --> 00:27:26,911
All right, Team Two will do that.

461
00:27:27,311 --> 00:27:29,615
What about Team One?
Let's go out, I'll treat you.

462
00:27:30,017 --> 00:27:31,150
Manager Seo, what will you do?

463
00:27:33,084 --> 00:27:34,209
I'll head home.

464
00:27:35,188 --> 00:27:36,188
Good work.

465
00:27:38,098 --> 00:27:41,255
I'm jealous.
We still have a lot left to do.

466
00:27:41,478 --> 00:27:42,478
Hang in there.

467
00:27:42,945 --> 00:27:45,145
We have no choice.
Let's push a little more.

468
00:27:47,466 --> 00:27:51,770
(Kangsu Construction)

469
00:28:14,493 --> 00:28:17,496
(Our Happy Days)

470
00:28:17,497 --> 00:28:18,501
Did you pull an all-nighter?

471
00:28:18,501 --> 00:28:20,111
I couldn't go home because of work.

472
00:28:20,111 --> 00:28:21,217
With Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

473
00:28:21,217 --> 00:28:22,218
Opportunity knocks.

474
00:28:22,218 --> 00:28:23,711
I have to find out why she took a break.

475
00:28:23,711 --> 00:28:24,736
Hey.

476
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:26,745
I don't know, I just like it.

477
00:28:26,745 --> 00:28:28,869
You know there are rumors going around...

478
00:28:28,869 --> 00:28:30,645
about the two of you
in the division, right?

479
00:28:30,645 --> 00:28:32,644
Rumors?

480
00:28:32,644 --> 00:28:34,513
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
